<p>I've problem with native code in Android.</p>  <p>I used this code to fill array with content from vector</p>  <pre><code>float * Map_Loader::ConvertToArray() {     float *arr = new float[(faces.size() -1)*3];     int index = 0, j = 0;     while(index &lt; faces.size())     {         arr[ j ] = faces[ index ].vertex[ 0 ].x;         arr[ j +1 ] = faces[ index ].vertex[ 1 ].y;         arr[ j +2 ] = faces[ index ].vertex[ 2 ].z;         j += 3;         index++;     }     return arr; } </code></pre>  <p>and I used this code to create pointer and get values from the function:</p>  <pre><code>float *x = Map.ConvertToArray(); </code></pre>  <p>It's working in windows , but in android I've problem..</p>  <p>Best regards</p>